<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Gavin Whyte scored a late equaliser with a header as ten-man Northern Ireland drew 1-1 with Romania in the Nations League.  </p>

<p>George Puscas had put Romania in the lead with 25 minutes gone.</p>

<p>Northern Ireland played much of the game with ten men after Josh Magennis was sent off in the 39th minute.</p>

<p>Arsenal youngster Daniel Ballard was given his senior debut for Ian Baraclough's side, while goalkeeper Bailey Peacock-Farrell made some outstanding saves.</p>

<p>More to follow...</p>

